{"title": "Ark in the Field",
"body": ["One morning you open", "one eye and listing to the south", "it bulks like a barn,", "noiseless, derelict", "planks horizontal and deeply grooved.", "A rudder the size of your front door", "pivots as you push. Once", "inside you can smell", "the fear of every winged,", "creeping and four-legged thing:", "no water, no straw,", "just shadow and bare wood.", "Where is the one promised", "to wake beside you forever?", "Ox-eyed daisies, goldenrod, clover\u2014", "why are you breathing", "among them, why don't you gather", "the outcast beasts or become one..."],
