{"title": "Do You Remember the Rude Nudists",
"body": ["Do you remember the rude nudists?", "Lazing easy in girth and tongue,", "wet slops and smacks of flesh as they buttered every crevice.", "Sungrunts. Blubberpalaver.", "We were always hiking some hill toward some beauty some", "human meanness ruined.", "We were always waiting too long to let ourselves be seen.", "It was an ocean's gesticulations, articulate elephant seals,", "grounded clouds grown all one mouth.", "What could we do but laugh,", "casting clothes aside as if the air were ice and water a warm bed,", "goose-stepping goose-pimpled past their appeased surprise into", "the waves.", "What could we do?", "We could\u2014we did\u2014love", "take a long look", "at each other", "and creep quietly away."],
