{"title": "Sonnet 13",
"body": ["I lift\u2014lift you five States away your glass,", "Wide of this bar you never graced, where none", "Ever I know came, where what work is done", "Even by these men I know not, where a brass", "Police-car sign peers in, wet strange cars pass,", "Soiled hangs the rag of day out over this town,", "A juke-box brains air where I drink alone,", "The spruce barkeep sports a toupee alas\u2014", "My glass I lift at six o'clock, my darling,", "As you plotted . . Chinese couples shift in bed,", "We shared today not even filthy weather,", "Beasts in the hills their tigerish love are snarling,", "Suddenly they clash, I blow my short ash red,", "Grey eyes light! and we have our drink together."],
