ody reaching", "in all its colors and lights\u2014", "your erotic face", "colored and lit\u2014", "not colored body-and-face", "but now entire,", "colors lights the world thinking and reaching.", "XI", "The river flows past the city.", "Water goes down to tomorrow", "making its children I hear their unborn voices", "I am working out the vocabulary of my silence.", "XII", "Big-boned man young and of my dream", "Struggles to get the live bird out of his throat.", "I am he am I? Dreaming?", "I am the bird am I? I am the throat?", "A bird with a curved beak.", "It could slit anything, the throat-bird.", "Drawn up slowly. The curved blades, not large.", "Bird emerges wet being born", "Begins to sing.", "XIII", "My night awake", "staring at the broad rough jewel", "the copper roof across the way", "thinking of the poet", "yet unborn in this dark", "who will be the throat of these hours.", "No. Of those hours.", "Who will speak these days,", "if not I,", "if not you?"],
