{"title": "High and Bright and Fine and",
"body": ["When the motorboat man asked me to love him", "I whispered", "the word for the no-more-boyfriend feeling", "because", "contains", "(practically twice)", "because I wanted teetering\u2014", "he said", "His ears from the engines\u2014so hard of hearing\u2014his hands always", "so hot", "Mid our first winter\u2014I\u2019d clung so long to the dock", "he had to crowbar my fingers off", "Each digit cracked so cleanly", "Would you say they break like", "? I asked sweetly", "I knew I was nothing! But if I could sustain one song\u2014", "I could be:", "Sex on the bathroom\u2019s cold marble counter was best", "I whispered", ",", "he, sculpting my legs, said", "The child? I named her", "It sounded like", "For pure, I said", "At the ocean, I said", "for vacation; for flowers,", "But when I said (only of late, late!)", "Brittle pearls broke behind my syllables", "Did he hear me?", "Again, twice, thrice:", "For my love", "we would need to live", "in a great pyramid", "We would need to sleep", "beneath the continental shelf", "with Antarctic crust blanketing us", "The only driveway to any kind of house", "is an iceberg-ridden Northwest Passage", "When I whispered", "you were to translate it as"],
