{"title": "The Duchess to Her Readers",
"body": ["A Poet am I neither born nor bred,", "But to a witty poet married:", "Whose brain is fresh and pleasant as the Spring,", "Where Fancies grow and where the Muses sing.", "There oft I lean my head, and listening, hark,", "To catch his words and all his fancies mark:", "And from that garden show of beauties take", "Whereof a posy I in verse may make.", "Thus I, that have no gardens of my own,", "There gather flowers that are newly blown."],
