{"title": "Last Hope",
"body": ["Beside a humble stone, a tree", "Floats in the cemetery\u2019s air,", "Not planted", "there,", "But growing wild, uncultured, free.", "A bird comes perching there to sing,", "Winter and summer, proffering", "Its faithful song\u2014sad, bittersweet.", "That tree, that bird are you and I:", "You, memory; absence, me, that tide", "And time record. Ah, by your side", "To live again, undying! Aye,", "To live again! But", ",", "Now nothingness, cold, owns my flesh. . .", "Will your love keep my memory fresh?"],
