{"title": "The Whip",
"body": ["I spent a night turning in bed,", "my love was a feather, a flat", "sleeping thing. She was", "very white", "and quiet, and above us on", "the roof, there was another woman I", "also loved, had", "addressed myself to in", "a fit she", "returned. That", "encompasses it. But now I was", "lonely, I yelled,", "but what is that? Ugh,", "she said, beside me, she put", "her hand on", "my back, for which act", "I think to say this", "wrongly."],
