{"title": "Rain",
"body": ["With thick strokes of ink the sky fills with rain.", "Pretending to run for cover but secretly praying for more rain.", "Over the echo of the water, I hear a voice saying my name.", "No one in the city moves under the quick sightless rain.", "The pages of my notebook soak, then curl. I\u2019ve written:", "\u201cYogis opened their mouths for hours to drink the rain.\u201d", "The sky is a bowl of dark water, rinsing your face.", "The window trembles; liquid glass could shatter into rain.", "I am a dark bowl, waiting to be filled.", "If I open my mouth now, I could drown in the rain.", "I hurry home as though someone is there waiting for me.", "The night collapses into your skin. I am the rain."],
