{"title": "For My Wife Cutting My Hair",
"body": ["You move around me expertly like the good, round", "Italian barber I went to in Florence,", "years before we met, his scissors", "a razor he sharpened on a belt.", "But at first when you were learning, I feared", "for my neck, saw my ears like sliced fruit", "on the newspapered floor. Taking us back in time,", "you cleverly clipped my head in a flat-top.", "The years in between were styles no one had ever seen,", "or should see again: when the wind rose", "half my hair floated off in feathers,", "the other half bristling, brief as a brush.", "In the chair, almost asleep, I hear the bright", "scissors dancing. Hear you hum, full-breasted as Aida,", "carefully trimming the white from my temples,", "so no one, not even I, will know."],
