{"title": "In the Cold Kingdom",
"body": ["Poised upside down on its duncecap,", "a shrunken purple head,", "True Blueberry,", "enters its tightening frame of orange lip,", "and the cream of a child\u2019s cheek is daubed with", "Zanzibar Cocoa, while", "Symbolistes.", "a fine green trickle\u2014", "Pistachio? Mint Julep?", "sweetens his chin.", "In front of me Licorice teeters like a lump of coal", "on its pinkish base of Pumpkin.", "donn\u00e9e", "Turning from all that is present", "in the flesh, so to speak,", "let the eye wander off to a menu,", "where it can start to ingest", "\u201cQuite Sour Lemon sherbet", "topped with a stem cherry and chocolate sprinkles", "all floating in bubbly cherry phosphate", "and served with a twist of pretzel.\u201d", "In this world \u201cCreamy Vanilla and", "Smooth Swiss Chocolate ice creams\u201d", "can be \u201cblended with chopped pineapple,", "dark fudge sauce, ripe bananas, whipped topping,", "cookies, roasted nutmeats and nippy chopped cherries.\u201d", "At about the moment my tastebuds", "receive a last tickle of Gingersnap", "and begin to respond to", "Orange Fudge, I look at you", "who have bought my ice cream cones for twenty years,", "and look away", "My mind assembles a ribald tower", "of sherbet dips, all on one cone,", "Apricot, Apple, Tangerine, Peach, Prune, Lime,", "and then it topples.", "You are steadier than I.", "You order one dip always,", "or, in a dish, two dips of the same flavor.", "In this hysterical brilliance of neon", "it is twelve or fifteen of us", "to thirty ice creams.", "Open the door, quick,", "and let in two handholding adolescents.", "Coping with all those glands", "makes them good and hungry.", "Listen! All around us toothsome cones", "are suffering demolition", "down to the last, nipple-like tip.", "How do we know where to stop?", "Perhaps the glasses and dishes", "are moulded of candy, and the counters and windows\u2026", "me"],
