{"title": "Snow",
"body": ["White people leave the express", "at 96th Street, collectively,", "like pigeons from a live wire", "or hope from the hearts of Harlem.", "And I\u2019m one of them, although", "my lover sleeps two stops north between", "Malcolm X and Adam Clayton Powell", "Boulevards, wishing my ass", "were cupped inside her knees and belly,", "wishing this in a dream thick", "with inequalities.", "I live on Riverside Drive. My face", "helped get me here. I was", "ruddy with anticipation the day", "I interviewed for the rooms", "near the park with its", "snow-covered maples. I was full", "of undisguised hope as I", "strolled along the river, believing", "I belonged there, that my people", "inherited this wonderland", "unequivocally, as if they deserved it.", "My lover buys twinkies from the Arabs,", "bootleg tapes on \u201825", ",", "and carries a blade in her back", "pocket although her hands", "are the gentlest I\u2019ve known.", "She ignores the piss smells", "on the corner, the sirens", "at 4 A.M., the men whose brains", "have dissolved in rum. And tries", "to trust a white woman who", "sleeps near the trees of Riverside.", "When we go out together,", "we avoid expensive", "caf\u00e9s on Columbus Avenue, jaunts", "to the Upper East Side. Harlem", "eyes us suspiciously or with", "contempt beneath half-closed lids.", "We have friends there,", "hidden in the ruins like gold, who", "accept us. When it snows,", "we walk boldly anywhere, as if the snow", "were a protection, or a death."],
