{"title": "Red Stains",
"body": ["In a pyloned desert where the scorpion reigns", "My love and I plucked poppies breathing tales", "Of crimes now long asleep, whose once\u2013red stains", "Dyed stabbing men, at sea with bloody sails.", "The golden sand drowsed. There a dog yelped loud;", "And in his cry rattled a hollow note", "Of deep uncanny knowledge of that crowd", "That loved and bled in winy times remote.", "The poppies fainted when the moon came wide;", "The cur lay still. Our passionate review", "Of red wise folly dreamed on . . . She by my side", "Stared at the Moon; and then I knew he knew.", "And then he smiled at", "; to him \u2019twas funny\u2014", "Her calm steel eyes, her earth\u2013old throat of honey!"],
