{"title": "Song",
"body": ["Sweet beast, I have gone prowling,", "a proud rejected man", "who lived along the edges", "catch as catch can;", "in darkness and in hedges", "I sang my sour tone", "and all my love was howling", "conspicuously alone.", "I curled and slept all day", "or nursed my bloodless wounds", "until the squares were silent", "where I could make my tunes", "singular and violent.", "Then, sure as hearers came", "I crept and flinched away.", "And, girl, you've done the same.", "A stray from my own type,", "led along by blindness,", "my love was near to spoiled", "and curdled all my kindness.", "I find no kin, no child;", "only the weasel's ilk.", "Sweet beast, cat of my own stripe,", "come and take my milk."],
