{"title": "We were Two Rooms of One Timber, But I Left that Place Alone",
"body": ["Henry pulled our heartwood along the rutted street", "that town stood beside, built two rooms", "and called them home. My Henry did that.", "There. And I lived all those days inside his love.", "But there is a kind of hunger that feeds", "on flesh. Only, let it be yearning, heaving,", "rising flesh. Only, let it be flesh living", "and loving. Alive. Let it be life.", "There is a kind of hunger that feeds on life.", "They carved into him with banquet knives,", "made stew of his skin and stirred it", "with his own bones. My Henry served: the meat", "and the pot to cook it in. And there was no charge", "against the men who made that meal."],
