{"title": "White Heliotrope",
"body": ["The feverish room and that white bed,", "The tumbled skirts upon a chair,", "The novel flung half-open, where", "Hat, hair-pins, puffs, and paints are spread;", "The mirror that has sucked your face", "Into its secret deep of deeps,", "And there mysteriously keeps", "Forgotten memories of grace;", "And you half dressed and half awake,", "Your slant eyes strangely watching me,", "And I, who watch you drowsily,", "With eyes that, having slept not, ache;", "This (need one dread? nay, dare one hope?)", "Will rise, a ghost of memory, if", "Ever again my handkerchief", "Is scented with White Heliotrope."],
"region": "England",
