{"title": "\"Love of My Flesh, Living Death\"",
"body": ["Once I wasn\u2019t always so plain.", "I was strewn feathers on a cross", "of dune, an expanse of ocean", "at my feet, garlands of gulls.", "Sirens and gulls. They couldn\u2019t tame you.", "You know as well as they: to be", "a dove is to bear the falcon", "at your breast, your nights, your seas.", "My fear is simple, heart-faced", "above a flare of etchings, a lineage", "in letters, my sudden stare. It\u2019s you.", "sang the heart upon its mantel", "pelvis. Blush of my breath, catch", "of my see\u2014beautiful bird\u2014It\u2019s you."],
