{"title": "Slow Dancing on the Highway:the Trip North",
"body": ["You follow close behind me,", "for a thousand miles responsive to my movements.", "I signal, you signal back. We will meet at the next exit.", "You blow kisses, which I return.", "You mouth \"I love you,\" a message for my rearview mirror.", "We do a slow tango as we change lanes in tandem,", "gracefully, as though music were guiding us.", "It is tighter than bodies locked in heat,", "this caring, this ardent watching."],
