{"title": "Amoretti XXIII: Penelope for her Ulisses sake",
"body": ["Penelope for her Ulisses sake,", "Deviz\u2019d a Web her wooers to deceave:", "In which the worke that she all day did make", "The same at night she did again unreave:", "Such subtile craft my Damzell doth conceave,", "Th\u2019 importune suit of my desire to shnone:", "For all that I in many dayes doo weave,", "In one short houre I find by her undonne.", "So when I thinke to end that I begonne,", "I must begin and never bring to end:", "For with one looke she spils that long I sponne,", "And with one word my whole years work doth rend.", "Such labour like the Spyders web I fynd,", "Whose fruitless worke is broken with least wynd."],
