{"title": "A Modest Love",
"body": ["The lowest trees have tops, the ant her gall,", "The fly her spleen, the little sparks their heat;", "The slender hairs cast shadows, though but small,", "And bees have stings, although they be not great;", "Seas have their source, and so have shallow springs;", "And love is love, in beggars as in kings.", "Where rivers smoothest run, deep are the fords;", "The dial stirs, yet none perceives it move;", "The firmest faith is in the fewest words;", "The turtles cannot sing, and yet they love:", "True hearts have eyes and ears, no tongues to speak;", "They hear and see, and sigh, and then they break."],
