{"title": "A Maul for Bill and Cindy\u2019s Wedding",
"body": ["Swung from the toes out,", "Belly-breath riding on the knuckles,", "The ten-pound maul lifts up,", "Sails in an arc overhead,", "And then lifts", "It floats, you float,", "For an instant of clear far sight\u2014", "Eye on the crack in the end-grain", "Angle of the oak round", "Stood up to wait to be split.", "The maul falls\u2014with a sigh\u2014the wood", "Claps apart", "and lies twain\u2014", "In a wink. As the maul", "Splits all, may", "You two stay together."],
