{"title": "Break of Day",
"body": ["\u2018Tis true, \u2018tis day, what though it be?", "O wilt thou therefore rise from me?", "Why should we rise because \u2018tis light?", "Did we lie down because \u2018twas night?", "Love, which in spite of darkness brought us hither,", "Should in despite of light keep us together.", "Light hath no tongue, but is all eye;", "If it could speak as well as spy,", "This were the worst that it could say,", "That being well I fain would stay,", "And that I loved my heart and honour so,", "That I would not from him, that had them, go.", "Must business thee from hence remove?", "Oh, that\u2019s the worst disease of love,", "The poor, the foul, the false, love can", "Admit, but not the busied man.", "He which hath business, and makes love, doth do", "Such wrong, as when a married man doth woo."],
"region": "England",
