{"title": "Cherry-Ripe",
"body": ["There is a garden in her face", "Where roses and white lilies blow;", "A heavenly paradise is that place,", "Wherein all pleasant fruits do flow:", "There cherries grow which none may buy", "Till \u201cCherry-ripe\u201d themselves do cry.", "Those cherries fairly do enclose", "Of orient pearl a double row,", "Which when her lovely laughter shows,", "They look like rose-buds filled with snow;", "Yet them no peer nor prince can buy", "Till \u201cCherry-ripe\u201d themselves do cry.", "Her eyes like angels watch them still;", "Her brows like bended bows do stand,", "Threat'ning with piercing frowns to kill", "All that attempt with eye or hand", "Those sacred cherries to come nigh,", "Till \u201cCherry-ripe\u201d themselves do cry."],
