{"title": "Auld Robin Forbes",
"body": ["And auld Robin Forbes hes gien tem a dance,", "I pat on my speckets to see them aw prance;", "I thout o\u2019 the days when I was but fifteen,", "And skipp\u2019d wi\u2019 the best upon Forbes\u2019s green.", "Of aw things that is I think thout is meast queer,", "It brings that that\u2019s by-past and sets it down here;", "I see Willy as plain as I dui this bit leace,", "When he tuik his cwoat lappet and deeghted his feace.", "The lasses aw wonder\u2019d what Willy cud see", "In yen that was dark and hard featur\u2019d leyke me;", "And they wonder\u2019d ay mair when they talk\u2019d o\u2019 my wit,", "And slily telt Willy that cudn\u2019t be it:", "But Willy he laugh\u2019d, and he meade me his weyfe,", "And whea was mair happy thro\u2019 aw his lang leyfe?", "It\u2019s e\u2019en my great comfort, now Willy is geane,", "The he offen said\u2014 nae place was leyke his awn heame!", "I mind when I carried my wark to yon steyle", "Where Willy was deykin, the time to beguile,", "He wad fling me a daisy to put i\u2019 my breast,", "And I hammer\u2019d my noddle to mek out a jest.", "But merry or grave, Willy often wad tell", "There was nin o\u2019 the leave that was leyke my awn sel;", "And he spak what he thout, for I\u2019d hardly a plack", "When we married, and nobbet ae gown to my back.", "When the clock had struck eight I expected him heame,", "And wheyles went to meet him as far as Dumleane;", "Of aw hours it telt", "was dearest to me,", "But now when it streykes there\u2019s a tear i\u2019 my ee.", "O Willy! dear Willy! it never can be", "That age, time, or death, can divide thee and me!", "For that spot on earth that\u2019s aye dearest to me,", "Is the turf that has cover\u2019d my Willy frae me!"],
