{"title": "Astrophil and Stella 90:",
"body": ["Stella, think not that I by verse seek fame,", "Who seek, who hope, who love, who live but thee;", "Thine eyes my pride, thy lips my history;", "If thou praise not, all other praise is shame.", "Nor so ambitious am I, as to frame", "A nest for my young praise in laurel tree:", "In truth I sweare, I wish not there should be", "Graved in mine epitaph a Poet\u2019s name:", "Nay if I would, could I just title make,", "That any laud to me thereof should grow,", "Without my plumes from others\u2019 wings I take.", "For nothing from my wit or will doth flow,", "Since all my words thy beauty doth endite,", "And love doth hold my hand, and makes me write."],
"region": "England",
"poet": "Sir Philip Sidney",
