{"title": "Astrophil and Stella 48:",
"body": ["Soul\u2019s joy, bend not those morning stars from me,", "Where virtue is made strong by beauty\u2019s might,", "Where love is chasteness, pain doth learn delight,", "And humbleness grows one with majesty.", "Whatever may ensue, O let me be", "Co-partner of the riches of that sight;", "Let not mine eyes be hell-driv\u2019n from that light;", "O look, O shine, O let me die and see.", "For though I oft my self of them bemoan,", "That through my heart their beamy darts be gone,", "Whose cureless wounds even now most freshly bleed,", "Yet since my death wound is already got,", "Dear killer, spare not they sweet cruel shot;", "A kind of grace it is to slay with speed."],
