{"title": "Mock Orange",
"body": ["It is not the moon, I tell you.", "It is these flowers", "lighting the yard.", "I hate them.", "I hate them as I hate sex,", "the man\u2019s mouth", "sealing my mouth, the man\u2019s", "paralyzing body\u2014", "and the cry that always escapes,", "the low, humiliating", "premise of union\u2014", "In my mind tonight", "I hear the question and pursuing answer", "fused in one sound", "that mounts and mounts and then", "is split into the old selves,", "the tired antagonisms. Do you see?", "We were made fools of.", "And the scent of mock orange", "drifts through the window.", "How can I rest?", "How can I be content", "when there is still", "that odor in the world?"],
