{"title": "Mannerly Margery Milk and Ale",
"body": ["Ay, beshrew you! by my fay,", "These wanton clerks be nice alway!", "Avaunt, avaunt, my popinjay!", "What, will ye do nothing but play?", "Tilly, vally, straw, let be I say!", "Gup, Christian Clout, gup, Jack of the Vale!", "With Mannerly Margery Milk and Ale.", "By God, ye be a pretty pode,", "And I love you an whole cart-load.", "Straw, James Foder, ye play the fode,", "I am no hackney for your rod:", "Go watch a bull, your back is broad!", "Gup, Christian Clout, gup, Jack of the Vale!", "With Mannerly Margery Milk and Ale.", "Ywis ye deal uncourteously;", "What, would ye frumple me? now fy!", "What, and ye shall be my pigesnye?", "By Christ, ye shall not, no hardely:", "I will not be jap\u00e8d bodily!", "Gup, Christian Clout, gup, Jack of the Vale!", "With Mannerly Margery Milk and Ale.", "Walk forth your way, ye cost me nought;", "Now have I found that I have sought:", "The best cheap flesh that I ever bought.", "Yet, for his love that all hath wrought,", "Wed me, or else I die for thought.", "Gup, Christian Clout, your breath is stale!", "Go, Mannerly Margery Milk and Ale!", "Gup, Christian Clout, gup, Jack of the Vale!", "With Mannerly Margery Milk and Ale."],
