{"title": "Love's Good-Morrow",
"body": ["Pack, clouds away! and welcome day!", "With night we banish sorrow;", "Sweet air, blow soft, mount larks aloft", "To give my love good-morrow!", "Wings from the wind to please her mind,", "Notes from the lark I\u2019ll borrow;", "Bird, prune thy wing, nightingale, sing,", "To give my love good-morrow;", "To give my love good-morrow;", "Notes from them both I\u2019ll borrow.", "Wake from thy nest, Robin Redbreast,", "Sing birds in every furrow;", "And from each hill, let music shrill", "Give my fair love good-morrow!", "Blackbird and thrush in every bush,", "Stare, linnet, and cock-sparrow!", "You pretty elves, amongst yourselves,", "Sing my fair love good-morrow;", "To give my love good-morrow,", "Sing birds in every furrow."],
"region": "England",
"poet": "Thomas Heywood",
