{"title": "Love\u2019s Philosophy",
"body": ["The fountains mingle with the river", "And the rivers with the ocean,", "The winds of heaven mix for ever", "With a sweet emotion;", "Nothing in the world is single;", "All things by a law divine", "In one spirit meet and mingle.", "Why not I with thine?\u2014", "See the mountains kiss high heaven", "And the waves clasp one another;", "No sister-flower would be forgiven", "If it disdained its brother;", "And the sunlight clasps the earth", "And the moonbeams kiss the sea:", "What is all this sweet work worth", "If thou kiss not me?"],
"region": "England",
"poet": "Percy Bysshe Shelley",
"period": "Romantic",
