{"title": "Idea 59:",
"body": ["As Love and I, late harbour\u2019d in one inn,", "With proverbs thus each other entertain:", "In love there is no lack, thus I begin,", "Fair words make fools, replieth he again;", "Who spares to speak, doth spare to speed (quoth I),", "As well (saith he) too forward, as too slow;", "Fortune assists the boldest, I reply,", "A hasty man (quoth he) ne\u2019er wanted woe;", "Labour is light, where love (quoth I) doth pay,", "(Saith he) light burthen\u2019s heavy, if far born;", "(Quoth I) the main lost, cast the bye away;", "You have spun a fair thread, he replies in scorn.", "And having thus awhile each other thwarted,", "Fools as we met, so fools again we parted."],
"region": "England",
