{"title": "Out of Catullus",
"body": ["Come and let us live my Deare,", "Let us love and never feare,", "What the sowrest Fathers say:", "Brightest", "that dies to day", "Lives againe as blithe to morrow,", "But if we darke sons of sorrow", "Set; o then, how long a Night", "Shuts the Eyes of our short light!", "Then let amorous kisses dwell", "On our lips, begin and tell", "A Thousand, and a Hundred, score", "An Hundred, and a Thousand more,", "Till another Thousand smother", "That, and that wipe of another.", "Thus at last when we have numbred", "Many a Thousand, many a Hundred;", "Wee\u2019l confound the reckoning quite,", "And lose our selves in wild delight:", "While our joyes so multiply,", "As shall mocke the envious eye."],
