{"title": "On a Girdle",
"body": ["That which her slender waist confin\u2019d,", "Shall now my joyful temples bind;", "No monarch but would give his crown,", "His arms might do what this has done.", "It was my heaven\u2019s extremest sphere,", "The pale which held that lovely deer,", "My joy, my grief, my hope, my love,", "Did all within this circle move.", "A narrow compass, and yet there", "Dwelt all that\u2019s good, and all that\u2019s fair;", "Give me but what this ribbon bound,", "Take all the rest the sun goes round."],
