{"title": "On a Dream",
"body": ["As Hermes once took to his feathers light,", "When lulled Argus, baffled, swoon\u2019d and slept,", "So on a Delphic reed, my idle spright", "So play\u2019d, so charm\u2019d, so conquer\u2019d, so bereft", "The dragon-world of all its hundred eyes;", "And seeing it asleep, so fled away,", "Not to pure Ida with its snow-cold skies,", "Nor unto Tempe where Jove griev\u2019d that day;", "But to that second circle of sad Hell,", "Where in the gust, the whirlwind, and the flaw", "Of rain and hail-stones, lovers need not tell", "Their sorrows\u2014pale were the sweet lips I saw,", "Pale were the lips I kiss\u2019d, and fair the form", "I floated with, about that melancholy storm."],
