{"title": "Never Love Unless",
"body": ["Never love unless you can", "Bear with all the faults of man:", "Men sometimes will jealous be", "Though but little cause they see;", "And hang the head, as discontent,", "And speak what straight they will repent.", "Men that but one saint adore", "Make a show of love to more.", "Beauty must be scorned in none,", "Though but truly served in one:", "For what is courtship but disguise?", "True hearts may have dissembling eyes.", "Men, when their affairs require,", "Must awhile themselves retire;", "Sometimes hunt, and sometimes hawk,", "And not ever sit and talk.", "If these and such-like you can bear,", "Then like, and love, and never fear!"],
