{"title": "The Affliction of Richard",
"body": ["Love not too much. But how,", "When thou hast made me such,", "And dost thy gifts bestow,", "How can I love too much?", "Though I must fear to lose,", "And drown my joy in care,", "With all its thorns I choose", "The path of love and prayer.", "Though thou, I know not why,", "Didst kill my childish trust,", "That breach with toil did I", "Repair, because I must:", "And spite of frighting schemes,", "With which the fiends of Hell", "Blaspheme thee in my dreams,", "So far I have hoped well.", "But what the heavenly key,", "What marvel in me wrought", "Shall quite exculpate thee,", "I have no shadow of thought.", "What am I that complain?", "The love, from which began", "My question sad and vain,", "Justifies thee to man."],
