{"title": "The Spider and the Ghost of the Fly",
"body": ["Once I loved a spider", "When I was born a fly,", "A velvet-footed spider", "With a gown of rainbow-dye.", "She ate my wings and gloated.", "She bound me with a hair.", "She drove me to her parlor", "Above her winding stair.", "To educate young spiders", "She took me all apart.", "My ghost came back to haunt her.", "I saw her eat my heart."],
