{"title": "The River at Wolf",
"body": ["Coming east we left the animals", "pelican beaver osprey muskrat and snake", "their hair and skin and feathers", "their eyes in the dark: red and green.", "Your finger drawing my mouth.", "that what they now have they once longed for.", "A day a year ago last summer", "God filled me with himself, like gold, inside,", "deeper inside than marrow.", "This close to God this close to you:", "walking into the river at Wolf with", "the animals. The snake\u2019s", "green skin, lit from inside. Our second life."],
