{"title": "The Lost Mistress",
"body": ["All\u2019s over, then: does truth sound bitter", "As one at first believes?", "Hark, \u2019tis the sparrows\u2019 good-night twitter", "About your cottage eaves!", "And the leaf-buds on the vine are woolly,", "I noticed that, today;", "One day more bursts them open fully", "\u2013 You know the red turns grey.", "Tomorrow we meet the same then, dearest?", "May I take your hand in mine?", "Mere friends are we, \u2013 well, friends the merest", "Keep much that I resign:", "For each glance of the eye so bright and black,", "Though I keep with heart\u2019s endeavor, \u2013", "Your voice, when you wish the snowdrops back,", "Though it stay in my soul for ever! \u2013", "Yet I will but say what mere friends say,", "Or only a thought stronger;", "I will hold your hand but as long as all may,", "Or so very little longer!"],
