{"title": "Yours & Mine",
"body": ["Through your lens the sequoia swallowed me", "like a dryad. The camera flashed & forgot.", "I, on the other hand, must practice my absent-", "mindedness, memory being awkward as a touch", "that goes unloved. Lately your eyes have shut", "down to a shade more durable than skin\u2019s. I know you", "love distance, how it smooths. You choose an aerial view,", "the city angled to abstraction, while I go for the close", "exposures: poorly-mounted countenances along Broadway,", "the pigweed cracking each hardscrabble backlot.", "It\u2019s a matter of perspective: yours is to love me", "from a block away & mine is to praise the grain-", "iness that weaves expressively: your face."],
