{"title": "Farewell Love and all thy Laws for ever",
"body": ["Farewell love and all thy laws forever;", "Thy baited hooks shall tangle me no more.", "Senec and Plato call me from thy lore", "To perfect wealth, my wit for to endeavour.", "In blind error when I did persever,", "Thy sharp repulse, that pricketh aye so sore,", "Hath taught me to set in trifles no store", "And scape forth, since liberty is lever.", "Therefore farewell; go trouble younger hearts", "And in me claim no more authority.", "With idle youth go use thy property", "And thereon spend thy many brittle darts,", "For hitherto though I have lost all my time,", "Me lusteth no lenger rotten boughs to climb."],
