{"title": "Modern Love: XVI",
"body": ["In our old shipwrecked days there was an hour,", "When in the firelight steadily aglow,", "Joined slackly, we beheld the red chasm grow", "Among the clicking coals. Our library-bower", "That eve was left to us: and hushed we sat", "As lovers to whom Time is whispering.", "From sudden-opened doors we heard them sing:", "The nodding elders mixed good wine with chat.", "Well knew we that Life's greatest treasure lay", "With us, and of it was our talk. \"Ah, yes!", "Love dies!\" I said: I never thought it less.", "She yearned to me that sentence to unsay.", "Then when the fire domed blackening, I found", "Her cheek was salt against my kiss, and swift", "Up the sharp scale of sobs her breast did lift:\u0097", "Now am I haunted by that taste! that sound!"],
