{"title": "Mediocrity in Love Rejected",
"body": ["Give me more love or more disdain;", "The torrid, or the frozen zone,", "Bring equal ease unto my pain;", "The temperate affords me none;", "Either extreme, of love, or hate,", "Is sweeter than a calm estate.", "Give me a storm; if it be love,", "Like Danae in that golden show'r", "I swim in pleasure; if it prove", "Disdain, that torrent will devour", "My vulture-hopes; and he's possess'd", "Of heaven, that's but from hell releas'd.", "Then crown my joys, or cure my pain;", "Give me more love, or more disdain."],
