{"title": "Lucinda Matlock",
"body": ["I went to the dances at Chandlerville,", "And played snap-out at Winchester.", "One time we changed partners,", "Driving home in the moonlight of middle June,", "And then I found Davis.", "We were married and lived together for seventy years,", "Enjoying, working, raising the twelve children,", "Eight of whom we lost", "Ere I had reached the age of sixty.", "I spun, I wove, I kept the house, I nursed the sick,", "I made the garden, and for holiday", "Rambled over the fields where sang the larks,", "And by Spoon River gathering many a shell,", "And many a flower and medicinal weed \u2014", "Shouting to the wooded hills, singing to the green valleys.", "At ninety-six I had lived enough, that is all,", "And passed to a sweet repose.", "What is this I hear of sorrow and weariness,", "Anger, discontent and drooping hopes?", "Degenerate sons and daughters,", "Life is too strong for you \u2014", "It takes life to love Life."],
