{"title": "Sonnet #10",
"body": ["You rose from our embrace and the small light spread", "like an aureole around you. The long parabola", "of neck and shoulder, flank and thigh I saw", "permute itself through unfolding and unlimited", "minuteness in the movement of your tall tread,", "the spine-root swaying, the Picasso-like \u00e9clat", "of scissoring slender legs. I knew some law", "of Being was at work. At one time I had said", "that love bestows such values, and so it does,", "but the old man in his canto was right and wise:", "Always I wanted to give and in wanting was", "the poet. A man now, aging, I know the best", "of love is not to bestow, but to recognize."],
