{"title": "Song: to Celia [\u201c",
"body": ["Drink to me only with thine eyes,", "And I will pledge with mine;", "Or leave a kiss but in the cup,", "And I\u2019ll not look for wine.", "The thirst that from the soul doth rise", "Doth ask a drink divine;", "But might I of Jove\u2019s nectar sup,", "I would not change for thine.", "I sent thee late a rosy wreath,", "Not so much honouring thee", "As giving it a hope, that there", "It could not withered be.", "But thou thereon didst only breathe,", "And sent\u2019st it back to me;", "Since when it grows, and smells, I swear,", "Not of itself, but thee."],
