{"title": "Sarah Brown",
"body": ["Maurice, weep not, I am not here under this pine tree.", "The balmy air of spring whispers through the sweet grass,", "The stars sparkle, the whippoorwill calls,", "But thou grievest, while my soul lies rapturous", "In the blest Nirvana of eternal light!", "Go to the good heart that is my husband,", "Who broods upon what he calls our guilty love: i", "Tell him that my love for you, no less than my love for him", "Wrought out my destiny i that through the flesh", "I won spirit, and through spirit, peace.", "There is no marriage in heaven,", "But there is love."],
