{"title": "Ye Flowery Banks (Bonie Doon)",
"body": ["Ye flowery banks o' bonie Doon,", "How can ye blume sae fair?", "How can ye chant, ye little birds,", "And I sae fu' o' care?", "Thou'll break my heart, thou bonie bird,", "That sings upon the bough;", "Thou minds me o' the happy days,", "When my fause love was true.", "Thou'll break my heart, thou bonie bird,", "That sings beside thy mate;", "For sae I sat, and sae I sang,", "And wist na o' my fate.", "Aft hae I rov'd by bonie Doon", "To see the wood-bine twine,", "And ilka bird sang o' its luve,", "And sae did I o' mine.", "Wi' lightsome heart I pu'd a rose", "Frae aff its thorny tree;", "And my fause luver staw my rose", "But left the thorn wi' me."],
